  N2 --> N3{PB: Process Builder - IF + CWB Lifecycle - Decide the recommended contingency plan using IF branching and policy thresholds; escalate to CWB if policy limits exceeded.}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Remote Functions (ERP writeback) + Process Builder - Transaction - Act: execute selected plan—create transport orders, inventory reservations, and packaging sequence updates with writebacks to SAP S/4HANA and notify carriers/3PLs.]
  N4 --> N5[PB: Process Builder - Notification + UI Screen (dashboard) - Notify operations, launch management, and carriers and surface decision rationale and key KPIs on launch dashboard for review.]
  N5 --> Z1[Outcome: Activated contingency minimizes OTIF impact while constraining incremental logistics cost; multi-echelon stock repositions and sequencing adjustments executed in SAP S/4HANA; operations and carrier partners notified; launch timeline preserved or minimally impacted.]
